<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="1333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1333">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860H. 48/12–1544: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the United States Political Adviser on the Staff of the Supreme
                                Allied Commander, Mediterranean Theater</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-20T19:00:00-04:00">December
                                    20, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>494. Department is in agreement with the position taken by you as stated
                            in your no. 1774 of December 15. We feel that any discussions <pb facs="1451" n="1441" xml:id="pg_1441"/> or negotiations with the
                            Yugoslavs should be conducted at some appropriate place where competent
                            US and British representatives can participate. We are still opposed to
                            any relaxation of our stand with respect to observers. We assume that if
                            SACMED is unable to obtain an agreement along the lines specified by the
                            CCS he will, in accordance with his instructions, so advise the CCS.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>